## Phase 5 | Anomaly Detector + /anomalies Endpoint

```bash
pip install requests

# Create anomaly_results table in PostgreSQL
kubectl exec -it postgres-postgresql-0 -n monitoring -- psql -U postgres -c "
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS anomaly_results (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    timestamp TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,
    cpu_percent FLOAT NOT NULL,
    anomaly BOOLEAN NOT NULL,
    message TEXT NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);"

# Run anomaly detector
python ml/anomaly_detector.py

# Verify data in database
kubectl exec -it postgres-postgresql-0 -n monitoring -- psql -U postgres -c "SELECT * FROM anomaly_results ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 10;"

# Stop Docker Compose backend (causes ghost process on port 8000)
docker compose -f docker/docker-compose.yml down

# Test /anomalies endpoint
curl http://localhost:8000/anomalies
curl "http://localhost:8000/anomalies?only_anomalies=true"

# Rebuild Docker image with updated backend
docker compose -f docker/docker-compose.yml build

git add ml/anomaly_detector.py Backend/app/routes/anomalies.py Backend/app/main.py Backend/requirements.txt start.sh database/init.sql
git commit -m "feat: Phase 5 complete - anomaly detector polling Prometheus, results stored in PostgreSQL, /anomalies endpoint added"
git push
```

**Anomaly detector flow:**
```
Prometheus (live CPU metrics)
        ↓
ml/anomaly_detector.py  (polls every 30s)
        ↓
FastAPI /predict  (Isolation Forest inference)
        ↓
PostgreSQL anomaly_results table
        ↓
GET /anomalies  (query results via API)
```

**Notable observation:** Docker restart captured in real time — CPU spike from 77% → 67% → 57% → 47% → 37% → 28% → 18% → 7% → 2.6% all correctly flagged as anomalies as the cluster recovered.

**Important:** Always run `docker compose -f docker/docker-compose.yml down` before `bash start.sh` to prevent ghost processes competing on port 8000.

**Result:** Full end-to-end pipeline working. Live cluster metrics flowing into AI model, results persisted and queryable via REST API.

